pl.myrecipebasket.model

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.myrecipebasket.model.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Entity
public class User
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Object User represents a person who created an account in MyRecipeBasket application and is using it to store and share links to recipes found on some external web sites.

    An User has:
    • username - a name that User have chosen to use within MyRecipeBasket application
    • email - an email address provided by User when creating account
    • password - a password provided by User when creating account
    • isActive - a flag which state if User is active and can perform User specific actions
    • roles - a list of Roles that have been assigned to User
    • ownRecipes - a list of Recipes added to MyRecipeBasket database by this User
    • favRecipes - a list of Recipes that this User added to his favorite section
    • votes - a list of Votes left by this User
    • comments - a list of Comments left by this User
    See Also:
    Role, Recipe, Vote, Comment, Serialized Form
